{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make Perimenopause Training Mandatory for All UK Doctors",
        "additional_details": "Too many women are told their symptoms are \u201cjust stress\u201d or prescribed antidepressants instead of receiving appropriate hormonal support. This can lead to worsening physical and mental health, impacting work, relationships and quality of life. Perimenopause is a natural stage of life, not a niche issue. Proper medical training could improve diagnosis, treatment and outcomes for millions of women across the UK.",
        "background": "Perimenopause affects millions of UK women, yet many are dismissed or misdiagnosed. We call for mandatory training for all doctors and at least one trained specialist in every GP practice to ensure women are properly recognised, supported and treated.",
